    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the African ethnic group of the same name inhabiting Cabinda province in Angola, Kinshasa region in Democratic Republic of Congo, and Brazzaville commune in Congo Republic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000044687/African Ethnonyms (1996)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para describir trabajos producidos por el grupo étnico africano del mismo nombre que habita la provincia de Cabinda en Angola, la región de Kinshasa en República Democrática de Congo y la comuna Brazzaville en República de Congo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken om werken te beschrijven van de gelijknamige Afrikaanse etnische groep die leeft in de provincie Cabinda in Angola, de regio Kinshasa in de Democratische Republiek Congo, en in Brazzaville in Congo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>描述非洲渥尤民族的文化風格。該民族分布在安哥拉的卡賓達省、剛果民主共和國的金夏沙地區，以及剛果共和國首都的布拉薩行政區。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
